SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized and the spinal column is dislocated from the skull and brain.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized and the head is removed from the body.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized and the blood of the body is replaced by a perfusate. (NCI)
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized and the body is drained of blood.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized, a lethal chemical is administered by injection and the body is drained of blood.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized, a lethal chemical is administered by intracardiac injection and the body is drained of blood.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Anesthetized Intracardiac Lethal Injection and Exsanguination Euthanasia

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized and a lethal chemical is administered by intracardiac injection to induce death.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized, a lethal chemical is administered by intraperitoneal injection and the body is drained of blood.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Anesthetized Intraperitoneal Lethal Injection and Exsanguination Euthanasia

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized and a lethal chemical is administered by intraperitoneal injection to induce death.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized, a lethal chemical is administered by intravenous injection and the body is drained of blood.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Anesthetized Lethal Injection Intravenous Exsanguination Euthanasia

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized and a lethal chemical is administered by intravenous injection to induce death.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is anesthetized and a lethal chemical is administered by injection to induce death.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is shot in the brain with a captive bolt pistol causing immediate and permanent unconsciousness or death, followed by draining the body of blood. (NCI)
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject inhales carbon dioxide until asphyxiation occurs and then the body is immediately drained of blood. (NCI)
A method of euthanasia whereby the spinal column is dislocated from the skull and brain.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject inhales carbon dioxide until death occurs.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject's head is removed from the body.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is given a lethal injection and the body is drained of blood.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is given a lethal intracardiac injection and the body is drained of blood.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Intracardiac Lethal Injection and Exsanguination Euthanasia

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is given a lethal intracardiac injection to induce death.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is given a lethal intraperitoneal injection and the body is drained of blood.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Intraperitoneal Lethal Injection and Exsanguination Euthanasia

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is given a lethal intraperitoneal injection to induce death.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is given a lethal intravenous injection and the body is drained of blood.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Intravenous Lethal Injection and Exsanguination Euthanasia

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is given a lethal intravenous injection to induce death.
A method of euthanasia whereby a subject is given a lethal injection to induce death.
